article.headline: William & Mary 61, N.C. Wilmington 55
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. (AP) -- Nathan Mann scored 25 points, including a pair of 3-pointers, to lead William & Mary to a 61-55 Colonial Athletic Association win Saturday over UNC-Wilmington. The win snapped a 12-game losing streak for the Tribe (14-11, 7-8 CAA) at Wilmington (6-18, 3-12). Mann was the only player in double figures for the Tribe, with the next highest scorers Alex Smith and David Schneider at 7 each. Montez Downey had 15 points for the Seahawks. Vladimir Kulhanin and Todd Henley had 12 points each. William & Mary trailed 29-27 at the half and went ahead when Mann scored 18 points in the second period and hit a jumper to put the Tribe ahead 56-54 with 2:10 left.
